WhatsApp was offline in large parts of the world on Wednesday night Picture: iStock Popular text messaging service WhatsApp went offline in large parts of the world on Wednesday night with reports on Down Detector and Twitter that users in Brazil the UK as well as the US were also experiencing issues. Android and iPhone devices were affected. Thousands have logged issues with the app through the Down Detector website with many taking to Twitter to express their anguish. By 11pm CAT there was no official information from the California-based company on the disruption. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share